<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14067">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Canoeing.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11595">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11595 mb-requirement-id-11596">
        (a) Review with your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in canoeing activities and what you should do to
        anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://boundarywaters.com/ely-minnesota-outfitter/canoe-trip-risks/"
          target="_blank"
          >Canoe Trip Risks (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bNlnEOblxLw" target="_blank"
          >Canoe Safety (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/a6Qy5sVRCtk" target="_blank"
          >Golden Rules of Canoeing | How To Stay Safe on the Water (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.bendingbranches.com/blogs/resources/round-up-of-our-best-canoeing-safety-topics"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety on Wilderness Canoe Trips (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11595 mb-requirement-id-11597">
        (b) Review prevention, symptoms, and first-aid treatment for the
        following injuries or illnesses that could occur while canoeing:
        blisters, cold-water shock and hypothermia, dehydration, heat-related
        illnesses, sunburn, sprains, and strains. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://paddlingmag.com/skills/how-to-prevent-and-treat-blisters/"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Prevent and Treat Blisters (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rH3gZuSr6Y8" target="_blank"
          >Cold Water Shock—How To Deal With Cold Water Shock (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pS0EeinLd3Y" target="_blank"
          >Cold Water Paddling Safely (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/EmNieKLjmH4" target="_blank"
          >What Happens If You Don't Drink Enough Water (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://paddling.com/learn/great-ways-to-beat-the-heat-and-avoid-heat-related-illness-on-the-water"
          target="_blank"
          >Great Ways To Beat the Heat and Avoid Heat-Related Illness on the
          Water (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://paddling.com/learn/what-to-do-if-you-are-overheated-after-a-paddling-this-summer"
          target="_blank"
          >What To Do if You Are Overheated After a Paddling This Summer?
          (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9aFm087_XWg" target="_blank"
          >What Causes Sunburns (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/z1gbB_peVDQ" target="_blank"
          >Sprain Care With RICE Method (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11595 mb-requirement-id-11598">
        (c) Discuss the Scouting America Safety Afloat policy. Tell how it
        applies to canoeing activities. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/safety-afloat/"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Afloat (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11599">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Before doing the following requirements, successfully complete the
      Scouting America swimmer test, found in the <i>Swimming</i> merit badge
      pamphlet.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11600">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11600 mb-requirement-id-11601">
        (a) Name and point out the major parts of a canoe. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qSGd6m-BOLM" target="_blank"
          >Basic Canoe Parts Identified (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/MqnFm-O7A5c" target="_blank"
          >The Parts of a Canoe (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yKg7UPmhv1w" target="_blank"
          >Parts of a Canoe (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11600 mb-requirement-id-11602">
        (b) Describe how the length and shape of a canoe affect its performance.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/PbBOp8PZiCg" target="_blank"
          >How To Choose the Right Canoe | Comparing Length, Width and Hull
          Shape (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nrZjyCH9zpA" target="_blank"
          >Canoe Design Features and How They Affect Performance (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11603">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11603 mb-requirement-id-11604">
        (a) Name and point out the parts of a paddle. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4KSwa6J3Jfw" target="_blank"
          >Parts of a Canoe Paddle Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11603 mb-requirement-id-11605">
        (b) Demonstrate how to correctly size a paddle for a paddler in a
        sitting position and a kneeling position.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11606">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11606 mb-requirement-id-11607">
        (a) Review with your counselor the characteristics of life jackets most
        appropriate for canoeing and tell why a life jacket must always be worn
        while paddling. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aFn7vB-ZHv8" target="_blank"
          >How To Pick &amp; Fit a PFD (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.nrs.com/learn/choose-the-right-life-jacket"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Choose the Right Life Jacket (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11606 mb-requirement-id-11608">
        (b) Demonstrate how to select and properly fit the correct size life
        jacket.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11606 mb-requirement-id-11609">
        (c) Review the importance of safety and rescue equipment such as a sound
        signal device, extra paddle, sponge, bailer, bilge pump, rescue sling,
        ropes, and throw bag. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fq6BvQTP9f0" target="_blank"
          >Essential Safety Gear for Canoeing (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://paddling.com/learn/13-pieces-of-essential-safety-equipment-for-ww-canoeing"
          target="_blank"
          >13 Pieces of Essential Safety Equipment for WW Canoeing (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11610">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Review with your counselor the general care and maintenance of canoes,
      paddles, and other canoeing equipment. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/A_-5fP3pYGo" target="_blank"
        >How To Check, Clean, and Dry Your Canoe (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/FPVAU5cpj88&amp;t=25" target="_blank"
        >Canoe Care and Maintenance (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/GIyZORTIbxw" target="_blank"
        >How To Care for an Ultralight Canoe (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11611">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      With a companion, use a properly equipped canoe to demonstrate the
      following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11611 mb-requirement-id-11612">
        (a) Safely carry and launch the canoe from a dock or shore (both, if
        possible). <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6xRWA9S0LEM" target="_blank"
          >How To Get Into and Out of a Canoe Smoothly and Safely (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11611 mb-requirement-id-11613">
        (b) Safely land the canoe on a dock or shore (both, if possible) and
        return it to its proper storage location.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11611 mb-requirement-id-11614">
        (c) Demonstrate kneeling and sitting positions in a canoe and explain
        the proper use for each position. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5lyRGXJsaGA&amp;t=20" target="_blank"
          >Should You Kneel or Sit in a Canoe? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11611 mb-requirement-id-11616">
        (d) Change places while afloat in the canoe. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GpBezA6dh5w" target="_blank"
          >How To Switch Places in a Canoe (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11615">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      With a companion, use a properly equipped canoe to demonstrate the
      following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11615 mb-requirement-id-11617">
        (a) Safely exit the canoe in deep water without losing contact with the
        canoe. Reenter the canoe with the assistance of the other paddler
        without capsizing the boat. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KAbv8CTZ8T0" target="_blank"
          >Getting Into a Canoe From Deep Water (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11615 mb-requirement-id-11618">
        (b) Safely perform a controlled capsize of the canoe and demonstrate how
        staying with a capsized canoe will support both paddlers. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/g3SR1WoDAt0" target="_blank"
          >How To Deal With a Flipped Canoe | Canoe Rescue Techniques (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GVXZFwHvfCE" target="_blank"
          >Capistrano Flip, Canoe Solo Self Rescue (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.boat-ed.com/blog/capsizing-a-canoe-what-to-do/"
          target="_blank"
          >Capsizing a Canoe: What To Do if It Happens to You (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11615 mb-requirement-id-11619">
        (c) Swim, tow, or push a swamped canoe 50 feet to shallow water. In the
        shallow water, empty the swamped canoe and reenter it. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://paddlingmag.com/skills/strokes-techniques/capistrano-flip-rescue-swamped-canoe/"
          target="_blank"
          >Rescue a Swamped Canoe With the Capistrano Flip (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/I8nMtYnshrg" target="_blank"
          >Unswamp a Canoe (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11615 mb-requirement-id-11620">
        (d) In deep water, rescue a swamped canoe and its paddlers. After
        checking that those in the water do not need immediate assistance, empty
        the swamped canoe and help the paddlers safely reenter their boat
        without capsizing. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Z_CEeqea41k" target="_blank"
          >Canoe Deep Water Rescue (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0vcuykiqmYc" target="_blank"
          >Open Canoe to Open Canoe Rescue (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11615 mb-requirement-id-11621">
        (e) Perform a canoe rescue of a conscious swimmer.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11615 mb-requirement-id-11622">
        (f) Using a rescue (throw) bag from shore, lay the line within 3 feet of
        a conscious swimmer 30 feet away. Show how to repack the bag when done.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/c-0MRc8_QJQ" target="_blank"
          >Swiftwater Rescue—Throw Bag Toss (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/eX_39_6PTOE" target="_blank"
          >Water Rescue: Throw Bags (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11623">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      With a companion, using a properly equipped canoe to demonstrate the
      following tandem maneuvers while paddling in unison on opposite sides and
      without changing sides. Each paddler must demonstrate these maneuvers in
      both the bow and stern and on both sides of the canoe while maintaining
      trim and balance of the canoe: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/ecStrF15o-4&amp;t=12" target="_blank"
        >3 Golden Rules of Canoeing Technique (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11623 mb-requirement-id-11624">
        (a) Pivot (spin) the canoe 180° (half circle) to the right from a
        stationary position, stop, and return to the starting position by
        pivoting to the left using draw and pushaway strokes or using forward
        and reverse sweeps staying within 2 boat lengths of the starting
        position. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Ytf5LMCkKwk" target="_blank"
          >Pivot Turns—Maneuvering a Canoe (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11623 mb-requirement-id-11625">
        (b) Move a canoe sideways (abeam) in one direction for 10 feet and then
        return to the starting position using the draw and pushaway strokes.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11623 mb-requirement-id-11626">
        (c) While in forward motion, stop the canoe within two boat lengths
        using the backstroke.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11623 mb-requirement-id-11627">
        (d) While in the stern position and without assistance from the bow
        paddler, paddle in a straight line 15-20 boat lengths using an
        appropriate steering stroke, e.g., the J-stroke or thumb-down rudder
        stroke with or without a stern pry. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kSOu0jyuqN8&amp;t=23" target="_blank"
          >How To Do a J-Stroke—Canoe Technique (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YpAB5p0ot5g" target="_blank"
          >Canoe tips with Chris Brain—The J stroke (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11623 mb-requirement-id-11628">
        (e) Move the canoe in a straight line 15-20 boat lengths with the bow
        paddler using as necessary the forward stroke, draw stroke or forward
        sweep and the stern paddler using an appropriate steering stroke, e.g.,
        the J-stroke or thumbdown rudder stroke with or without a stern pry.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rjdlF7Cnr3E" target="_blank"
          >Tandem Canoe Basics (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aDaqvoIJD-A" target="_blank"
          >How To Paddle a Tandem Canoe (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11623 mb-requirement-id-11629">
        (f) While maintaining forward motion, turn the canoe 90° in an arc to
        the right in 5-10 boat lengths with the bow paddler using as necessary
        either the draw stroke or forward sweep and the stern paddler using only
        the forward stroke. Repeat the maneuver turning the canoe 90° to the
        left.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11623 mb-requirement-id-11630">
        (g) Move the canoe backwards in a straight line 3-4 boat lengths using
        as necessary the back stroke, reverse sweep or draw stroke in the bow or
        the stern. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/48ihzYwWn1w" target="_blank"
          >Canoeing—How To Paddle Straight Back (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11623 mb-requirement-id-11631">
        (h) Complete a figure of 8 course around markers 3-4 boat lengths apart
        using appropriate strokes including the draw stroke, and the forward and
        reverse sweeps.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
